Hi @airthomas!

When setting up the column selector, the default setting of `columnSelector_mediaquery` is `true` which requires  that `data-priority` attributes are set for each header. Setting it to `false` allows hidding columns. I'll make this more clear in the documentation.

```js
$(function() {

	$("table").tablesorter({debug: true,
		theme: 'blue',
		widgets: ['columnSelector'],
		widgetOptions : {
			columnSelector_mediaquery: false,
			columnSelector_columns: {
				0: false,
				2: false
			}
		}
	});

});
```

Also, the [demo](http://jsfiddle.net/Mottie/3pS6v/223/) won't work unless the `widget-columnSelector.js` file is loaded.

It's not documented, but you can add an `appender` option - this is what the pager does to intercept rendering, so make sure to add your code after the pager has initialized otherwise the pager will replace it ([demo](https://jsfiddle.net/Mottie/bbxxomhx/475/)).

```js
$('table').tablesorter({
  appender: function(table, rows) {
    $(table).find('tbody').append(rows);
    // make sure to trigger an "updateComplete" or some widgets
    // may not function properly
    $(table).trigger('updateComplete');
  }
});
```

