https://carto.com/docs/carto-engine/maps-api/anonymous-maps/

Full example:
With this mapconfig:
```json
{
  "version": "1.3.0",
  "layers": [{
    "type": "mapnik",
    "options": {
      "cartocss_version": "2.1.1",
      "cartocss": "#layer { polygon-fill: #F00; }",
      "sql": "select * from laspalmas"
    }
  }]
}
```

```sh
curl -X POST https://javitonino.carto.com/api/v1/map?api_key=XXX -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d @config
```

```json
{
    "layergroupid": "e93018f5a9e649c4f15de972c48f81be:1503650119071",
    "metadata": {
        "layers": [
            {
                "type": "mapnik",
                "id": "layer0",
                "meta": {
                    "cartocss": "#layer { polygon-fill: #F00; }",
                    "stats": {
                        "estimatedFeatureCount": 34
                    },
                    "cartocss_meta": {
                        "rules": []
                    }
                }
            }
        ],
        "dataviews": {},
        "analyses": []
    },
    "cdn_url": {
        "templates": {
            "http": {
                "url": "http://{s}.ashbu.cartocdn.com",
                "subdomains": [
                    "0",
                    "1",
                    "2",
                    "3"
                ]
            },
            "https": {
                "url": "https://cartocdn-ashbu_{s}.global.ssl.fastly.net",
                "subdomains": [
                    "a",
                    "b",
                    "c",
                    "d"
                ]
            }
        },
        "http": "ashbu.cartocdn.com",
        "https": "cartocdn-ashbu.global.ssl.fastly.net"
    },
    "last_updated": "2017-08-25T08:35:19.071Z"
}
```

Then it's exactly the same as with named maps.

To get a static image:
`https://javitonino.carto.com/api/v1/map/static/center/e93018f5a9e649c4f15de972c48f81be:1503650119071/6/29/-15/200/200.png?api_key=XXX`

Or an interactive map, use a vizjson like so: https://gist.github.com/javitonino/742afe514ce22d846e0762fe23f4f295

Something important to note is that I thought that you could pass the layergroupid directly to cartodb.js for rendering, but it seems that I was completely mistaken, you need to either pass a named map template or a vizjson + api_key. There is another trick, which is to treat the anonymous map as a tiled layer, but it also needs the api key, and we lose the opportunity to add legends/tooltips, etc.

So, sorry for misleading you, I really thought that anonymous maps were usable. After this, maybe it's not such a great idea then to do this, since the api_key would be in the generated HTML. 🤔

