Having read your comments in thread #164 I think I've come up with a hacky way to select ingredients using the commandline.

For a bit of background, I've just started using sacred (and really like what I've seen so far!) and want to use it for tracking my deep learning experiments. In particular, I may develop a network which I want to use on different datasets. This would work perfectly with your Ingredients framework if it were slightly more flexible. I wanted to put each dataset loader in different files as an ingredient, and choose which one to load into my experiment at run time. Unfortunately, I can't see a way to add Ingredients after an experiment has been declared, and I only want to add one dataset to an experiment rather than adding them all each time.

So here's how I think we can work around the current interface:
   
```python
from sacred import Experiment
import argparse
parser = argparse.ArgumentParser()
parser.add_argument('-a', action='store_true', help='switch ingredients')

if __name__=='__main__':
    # add the ingredient while creating the experiment
    flags, unparsed = parser.parse_known_args()
    if flags.a:
        from dataset1 import data_ingredient, load_data
    else:
        from dataset2 import data_ingredient, load_data
    ex = Experiment(ingredients=[data_ingredient])

@ex.config
